00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:49,678
I started tango as a hobby,

257
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:51,263
and I fell in love with it.

258
00:23:51,888 --> 00:23:53,890
You do it as a hobby,
and you're that good?

259
00:23:54,808 --> 00:23:55,642
Wow.

260
00:23:55,725 --> 00:23:56,560
My goodness.

261
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:13,285
You know Han So-ra, right?

262
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:14,995
She's in our class too.

263
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:18,874
Does Ms. Han

264
00:24:19,457 --> 00:24:21,668
not like to mingle with other people?

265
00:24:22,586 --> 00:24:24,087
Well, everybody knows

266
00:24:24,171 --> 00:24:26,256
that ex-Prime Minister Han
didn't teach her any manners.

267
00:24:27,507 --> 00:24:29,843
She was the parent representative
when her older kid went here,

268
00:24:29,926 --> 00:24:31,428
and she didn't even
look at the other moms.

269
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:33,972
She's too good for us, apparently.

270
00:24:35,265 --> 00:24:36,391
No way.

271
00:24:36,474 --> 00:24:39,186
Is she going to be
the parent representative again?

272
00:24:39,269 --> 00:24:40,645
She's too old for that.

273
00:24:40,729 --> 00:24:43,064
-Somebody around our age should do it.
-That's true.

274
00:24:44,191 --> 00:24:46,193
Maybe you'll do it this time.

275
00:24:52,782 --> 00:24:53,617
Hello.

276
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:56,578
Yes.

277
00:24:58,205 --> 00:24:59,789
Can you come to the front gate?

278
00:25:01,625 --> 00:25:02,500
Okay.

279
00:25:04,544 --> 00:25:06,213
The flowers that I ordered are here.

280
00:25:06,296 --> 00:25:07,214
Excuse me for a moment.

281
00:25:55,512 --> 00:25:56,638
Hello, sir.

282
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:58,306
You're here for the delivery, right?

283
00:26:00,475 --> 00:26:01,434
Ta-da.

284
00:26:02,352 --> 00:26:04,271
What are you doing here?

285
00:26:04,354 --> 00:26:05,772
I thought you were working late today.

286
00:26:05,855 --> 00:26:08,566
I came to see you as soon as I was done.

287
00:26:10,860 --> 00:26:12,654
Congratulations on your performance.

288
00:26:17,534 --> 00:26:19,411
I wish I got to see you dance.

289
00:26:19,494 --> 00:26:20,745
What a shame.

290
00:26:28,837 --> 00:26:30,088
You missed the performance,

291
00:26:32,132 --> 00:26:35,385
but you get to see something
that nobody else can see.

292
00:27:05,665 --> 00:27:09,044
WAITING ROOM FOR FEMALE PERFORMERS

293
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:19,304
Mom, Dad.

294
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:23,600
Mom, I'm friends with Da-bi now.

295
00:27:23,683 --> 00:27:26,811
Da-bi wants to learn ballet
from you too, just like me.

296
00:27:27,395 --> 00:27:28,521
Really?

297
00:27:28,605 --> 00:27:30,607
Yes. You're so pretty.

298
00:27:31,524 --> 00:27:33,902
If your parents agree to it,
you can learn from me.

299
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:34,819
Okay.

300
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:40,075
Did you have fun, Da-bi?

301
00:27:41,451 --> 00:27:43,161
Mom, I made a new friend.

302
00:27:43,828 --> 00:27:44,662
Did you, now?

303
00:27:46,581 --> 00:27:49,459
I told you not to make friends
with the poor kids, didn't I?

304
00:27:50,293 --> 00:27:51,920
I'll pick out your friends for you.

305
00:27:58,885 --> 00:27:59,969
Director Kang?

306
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:05,141
Director Kang.

307
00:28:05,225 --> 00:28:06,935
Wait, you're the chairman now.

308
00:28:07,018 --> 00:28:08,937
I haven't seen you in a while, sir.

309
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:10,647
Assistant Manager Jang?

310
00:28:11,231 --> 00:28:12,857
I'm actually a general manager now.

311
00:28:12,941 --> 00:28:15,151
I've been in Seoul
for more than eight years now.

312
00:28:16,152 --> 00:28:18,405
He was the branch manager
when I was in Argentina.

313
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:21,866
Nice to meet you, ma'am.

314
00:28:25,912 --> 00:28:28,289
I guess it really is a small world.

315
00:28:29,541 --> 00:28:31,751
It's a pleasure to meet you, sir.

316
00:28:31,835 --> 00:28:32,836
And you too, ma'am.

317
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:36,714
This is my wife and my daughter, Bo-ram.

318
00:28:39,300 --> 00:28:40,677
Hello.

319
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:43,680
I enjoyed your performance.

320
00:28:43,763 --> 00:28:45,098
Thank you.

321
00:28:54,816 --> 00:28:56,609
Da-bi, do you want something to eat?

322
00:28:57,902 --> 00:28:59,821
Do you want this?

323
00:29:38,485 --> 00:29:40,737
-Hello, Mr. Prime Minister.
-Hello.

324
00:29:40,820 --> 00:29:43,198
I haven't seen you
since my oldest granddaughter graduated.

325
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:46,034
Liyan has come a long way since then.

326
00:29:46,117 --> 00:29:47,494
It's all thanks to you, sir.

327
00:29:48,369 --> 00:29:51,122
-Liyan is looking great.
-Thank you.

328
00:29:52,582 --> 00:29:53,458
What is it?

329
00:29:53,541 --> 00:29:56,961
The chairman of the foundation
and ex-Prime Minister Han are here.

330
00:29:57,045 --> 00:29:59,339
We'll assist you soon.
Please wait just a moment.

331
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:01,925
Why aren't we moving, Mom?

332
00:30:02,008 --> 00:30:04,511
Yes, I wonder why.

333
00:30:05,553 --> 00:30:07,680
Bo-ram, I'll be right back.

334
00:30:08,848 --> 00:30:09,974
Wait in the car.

335
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:12,060
Gosh, so we don't even matter?

336
00:30:12,143 --> 00:30:15,146
Are we to expect this kind of treatment
all throughout?

337
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:16,815
This is pissing me off!

338
00:30:17,524 --> 00:30:19,984
How can you discriminate
between people like this?

339
00:30:20,068 --> 00:30:22,320
Seriously, you have to be kidding me.

340
00:30:22,403 --> 00:30:24,697
Do you know how much money
I spent on this school?

341
00:30:25,406 --> 00:30:27,784
-I'm sorry.
-Open the gate right now.

342
00:30:27,867 --> 00:30:29,577
We'll assist you soon.
Please wait just a moment.

343
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:31,788
Wait for how long? Just open it already!

344
00:30:31,871 --> 00:30:34,958
You get prettier every time I see you.

345
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:37,836
All thanks to Mr. Han here,

346
00:30:37,919 --> 00:30:40,630
Liyan has become one of
the best kindergartens in the world.

347
00:30:50,390 --> 00:30:51,975
-Dad!
-Honey!

348
00:30:52,058 --> 00:30:53,726
-Stop!
-Honey!

349
00:30:53,810 --> 00:30:54,978
Dad!

350
00:30:55,061 --> 00:30:56,688
Just sign it, you idiot!

351
00:30:57,814 --> 00:31:00,900
Now that you've got him,
he'll confess in no time, sir.

352
00:31:00,984 --> 00:31:03,069
The higher-ups won't let me do it.

353
00:31:06,072 --> 00:31:08,116
You little brat.

354
00:31:08,825 --> 00:31:10,785
If your dad doesn't sign it,

355
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,787
he's going to die.

356
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:15,331
-Honey!
-Dad!

357
00:31:15,999 --> 00:31:17,208
It's okay.

358
00:31:17,292 --> 00:31:18,126
Get it from the inside.

359
00:31:18,209 --> 00:31:20,545
-It's okay. Just a bit more.
-It's okay.

360
00:31:20,628 --> 00:31:21,462
Come on!

361
00:31:22,797 --> 00:31:24,841
Just a bit more.

362
00:31:24,924 --> 00:31:25,884
From the inside.

363
00:31:25,967 --> 00:31:27,010
-It's okay.
-It's good now.

364
00:31:27,093 --> 00:31:29,304
-Hurry up!
-We got it, we're done.

365
00:31:29,387 --> 00:31:31,180
-All right.
-We're done.

366
00:31:31,264 --> 00:31:32,265
No, a bit more.

367
00:31:32,348 --> 00:31:33,224
There, done.

368
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:44,152
If it says Han Pan-ro,
everybody will know.

369
00:32:00,919 --> 00:32:02,503
This is to show our gratitude.

370
00:32:03,463 --> 00:32:04,297
HAN PAN-RO

371
00:32:04,380 --> 00:32:05,840
The donations that you gave us

372
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:08,092
were used to remodel the gymnasium.

373
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:09,844
That's good to hear.

374
00:32:14,140 --> 00:32:17,894
Wow, this space has gotten a lot bigger.

375
00:32:17,977 --> 00:32:20,396
The kids will love running around here.

376
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:24,233
We've built a climbing wall
that's suitable for children.

377
00:32:24,734 --> 00:32:26,819
Wow, I've never seen this.

378
00:32:27,820 --> 00:32:29,197
This looks great.

379
00:32:30,907 --> 00:32:32,367
This looks fun.

380
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:33,284
Right?

381
00:32:41,292 --> 00:32:44,504
This is a classroom that was set up
so that our students

382
00:32:44,587 --> 00:32:47,799
can get the best education
in a comfortable setting.

383
00:32:47,882 --> 00:32:51,386
They'll learn how to play
all of the instruments.

384
00:32:51,469 --> 00:32:52,887
Even right now, our students

385
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:56,766
are getting numerous awards
in competitions all over the world.

386
00:32:56,849 --> 00:32:58,977
Like so, we're producing
the finest students

387
00:32:59,060 --> 00:33:00,853
in every single category.

388
00:33:00,937 --> 00:33:03,940
Since you're working so hard
for the children,

389
00:33:04,023 --> 00:33:06,567
maybe I should build
a horseback riding center next time.

390
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:08,569
I would be grateful.

391
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:10,405
You're going to make another donation?

392
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:11,614
-Yes.
-But you don't have

393
00:33:11,698 --> 00:33:12,949
any more grandchildren.

394
00:33:13,032 --> 00:33:15,368
What are you talking about?
I'm still waiting on a grandson.

395
00:33:16,452 --> 00:33:17,495
Right, So-ra?

396
00:33:18,746 --> 00:33:20,540
Oh, come on.

397
00:34:02,623 --> 00:34:05,293
Thank you so much for visiting us today.

398
00:34:07,253 --> 00:34:09,380
You've worked so hard for this place.

399
00:34:09,464 --> 00:34:10,673
I mean, just look at this.

400
00:34:11,382 --> 00:34:14,052
-It's all thanks to you, sir.
-Oh, don't say that.

401
00:34:14,135 --> 00:34:17,847
This place will look even greater
with a horseback riding center.

402
00:34:17,930 --> 00:34:19,932
No, I'm going to build that
next to my house.

403
00:34:23,352 --> 00:34:26,397
Da-bi, make sure to study hard
and become a great person, okay?

404
00:34:26,939 --> 00:34:27,774
Okay.

405
00:34:28,357 --> 00:34:30,276
Should we get going now, Da-bi?

406
00:34:30,359 --> 00:34:31,360
Let's go.

407
00:34:31,444 --> 00:34:32,528
This way please.

408
00:34:54,801 --> 00:34:58,513
His political book was a huge hit,
and loved especially by the millennials.

409
00:34:59,138 --> 00:35:00,389
Here with us today,

410
00:35:00,473 --> 00:35:02,391
please welcome Congressman Seo Eun-pyeong.

411
00:35:03,726 --> 00:35:08,648
THE MAN WHO OPENED A NEW POLITICAL HOTSPOT

412
00:35:08,731 --> 00:35:10,733
Hello, I'm Seo Eun-pyeong.

413
00:35:11,818 --> 00:35:13,069
Well…

414
00:35:14,195 --> 00:35:15,196
My book is titled

415
00:35:15,279 --> 00:35:17,240
The Man Who Opened
A New Political Hotspot.

416
00:35:17,323 --> 00:35:21,452
But if you came here today expecting me
to introduce you to a new hotspot,

417
00:35:22,870 --> 00:35:24,789
you might be disappointed.

418
00:35:25,706 --> 00:35:29,252
SEO EUN-PYEONG'S FALL BOOK FESTIVAL

419
00:35:29,335 --> 00:35:32,964
I actually wrote this book
during the darkest period of my life.

420
00:35:33,047 --> 00:35:36,217
I'd given up a lot of things
when I was studying for my exams.

421
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:38,344
Dating, marriage, getting a child,

422
00:35:38,427 --> 00:35:40,263
buying my own house, and friends.

423
00:35:40,346 --> 00:35:42,348
I gave up on all such things.

424
00:35:42,431 --> 00:35:44,725
I didn't have anyone to meet up with,
and I was broke.

425
00:35:44,809 --> 00:35:47,979
So I came up with
thousands of ideas at home by myself.

426
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:50,189
Then I wrote a book like this,

427
00:35:50,273 --> 00:35:53,025
and it helped me earn a lot of money.

428
00:35:54,026 --> 00:35:57,029
But it's more than just this book.

429
00:35:58,322 --> 00:36:00,992
If I ever lose my job as a politician,

430
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:03,703
I'll just open a small restaurant nearby

431
00:36:03,786 --> 00:36:06,497
and give you guys a 50 percent discount.

432
00:36:07,165 --> 00:36:09,458
Then maybe people will come
out of sheer curiosity.

433
00:36:09,542 --> 00:36:12,461
And then it'll gain popularity,

434
00:36:13,337 --> 00:36:16,674
and then just maybe it'll make a huge hit.

435
00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:23,389
So what am I really trying to say here?

436
00:36:23,472 --> 00:36:24,515
Giving up?

437
00:36:25,099 --> 00:36:26,601
I gave up on things too.

438
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:29,770
But don't start getting used to it.

439
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:32,356
Don't start giving up
your hopes and dreams too.

440
00:36:33,065 --> 00:36:35,151
I don't know how you're feeling right now

441
00:36:35,234 --> 00:36:37,236
or what you're doing with your lives.

442
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:38,696
But what you do in the present

443
00:36:38,779 --> 00:36:42,200
will become a great skill for you,
ten years in the future.

444
00:36:42,283 --> 00:36:45,119
Just like me, standing in front of you.

445
00:36:46,412 --> 00:36:49,415
So never give up.

446
00:36:49,957 --> 00:36:50,791
We can do this,

447
00:36:51,584 --> 00:36:52,752
everyone.

448
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:56,964
Thank you.

449
00:37:11,562 --> 00:37:13,522
-Hello.
-Oh, hello.

450
00:37:13,606 --> 00:37:15,858
-Are you Mr. Seo Eun-pyeong?
-Yes, I am.

451
00:37:15,942 --> 00:37:18,027
This is for you, from the United States.

452
00:37:19,737 --> 00:37:21,280
Could you sign this right here?

453
00:37:22,782 --> 00:37:24,784
-Thank you.
-No problem. Thank you.

454
00:38:02,363 --> 00:38:03,197
IT'S LEE LA-EL

455
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:04,657
THIS IS TEN TIMES
WHAT I GOT FROM YOU, AS PROMISED

456
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:06,242
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING
THAT YOU'VE DONE FOR ME

457
00:38:08,995 --> 00:38:09,829
Lee La-el.

458
00:38:11,455 --> 00:38:14,375
13 YEARS AGO

459
00:38:18,713 --> 00:38:21,299
Are we allowed to come here
without any prior approval?

460
00:38:21,382 --> 00:38:23,467
Shouldn't we officially request a visit?

461
00:38:24,218 --> 00:38:26,053
Come on, I'm scared.

462
00:38:26,137 --> 00:38:28,806
You think they'll let me in
on the investigation if I send a request?

463
00:38:28,889 --> 00:38:32,727
You don't know if Mr. Lee
is at the NIS or a police station.

464
00:38:32,810 --> 00:38:34,312
We need to be sure--

465
00:38:36,439 --> 00:38:37,273
Are you all right?

466
00:38:41,527 --> 00:38:42,361
Are you okay?

467
00:38:48,868 --> 00:38:50,703
We're in front of
Ms. Han So-ra's residence.

468
00:38:50,786 --> 00:38:53,122
Her husband, Mr. Kang Yoon-gyeom,

469
00:38:53,205 --> 00:38:56,042
is the heir of LY Group,
which will soon acquire GEDIKS

470
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:57,543
and become a global enterprise.

471
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:02,840
LY CURRENTLY IN 30TH PLACE,
WILL IT BECOME A CONGLOMERATE?

472
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:07,845
You're early.

473
00:39:09,722 --> 00:39:10,556
Yes.

474
00:39:12,850 --> 00:39:14,393
You're not looking too good.

475
00:39:16,937 --> 00:39:18,356
I know it's for your safety,

476
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:22,985
but I wish I didn't have to send you

477
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,488
to another country all alone.

478
00:39:25,571 --> 00:39:27,281
It's all right.

479
00:39:31,660 --> 00:39:32,495
I…

480
00:39:33,662 --> 00:39:36,665
I was worried since it's hard
to get a Bar Association scholarship.

481
00:39:37,792 --> 00:39:39,001
But you have great grades.

482
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:45,841
Thank you, sir.

483
00:39:47,176 --> 00:39:48,636
I'll never forget your kindness.

484
00:39:52,306 --> 00:39:53,140
And…

485
00:40:01,023 --> 00:40:01,982
Lee La-el.

486
00:40:04,568 --> 00:40:05,403
Lee La-el.

487
00:40:06,987 --> 00:40:09,949
I've never called you by your name before.

488
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:12,118
It's a pretty name.

489
00:40:13,327 --> 00:40:16,163
Is there a meaning behind it?

490
00:40:21,585 --> 00:40:22,753
"A person who belongs to God."

491
00:40:25,131 --> 00:40:26,382
My dad named me.

492
00:40:27,967 --> 00:40:29,385
A person who belongs to God.

493
00:40:37,309 --> 00:40:38,144
Here.

494
00:40:38,811 --> 00:40:41,188
If you ever need help
in the States, call me.

495
00:40:41,272 --> 00:40:42,106
It's a new number.

496
00:40:43,232 --> 00:40:44,817
I don't have a law office anymore.

497
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:47,611
Why don't you have one?

498
00:40:48,654 --> 00:40:50,364
I'm not going to be a lawyer anymore.

499
00:40:51,449 --> 00:40:53,826
I want to live a different life.

500
00:40:55,327 --> 00:40:56,162
Why?

501
00:40:59,165 --> 00:41:00,833
I wanted to help people.

502
00:41:02,418 --> 00:41:04,587
That's why I became a human rights lawyer.

503
00:41:06,213 --> 00:41:07,590
But I realized something

504
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:10,843
after seeing what happened to your family.

505
00:41:12,386 --> 00:41:13,679
If I don't have any power,

506
00:41:16,056 --> 00:41:17,266
then I can't help anybody.

507
00:41:18,434 --> 00:41:19,268
I wonder…

508
00:41:22,855 --> 00:41:25,399
what kind of person you'll become.

509
00:41:25,483 --> 00:41:27,026
And I also want to know

510
00:41:29,278 --> 00:41:30,571
what your life will be like.

511
00:41:32,406 --> 00:41:34,241
Although it won't be the same as before.

512
00:41:35,242 --> 00:41:36,243
Probably not.

513
00:41:38,662 --> 00:41:39,705
As time passes,

514
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,459
I'll most likely be forgotten.

515
00:41:47,630 --> 00:41:48,464
But someday,

516
00:41:52,009 --> 00:41:54,428
when people start talking
about their misfortunes,

517
00:41:54,512 --> 00:41:55,846
take a moment to think of me.

518
00:41:55,930 --> 00:41:57,264
HAN SO-RA'S HUSBAND
CHAIRMAN OF LY, KANG YOON-GYEOM

519
00:41:58,307 --> 00:41:59,850
Because I'm going to pay them back…

520
00:42:07,233 --> 00:42:08,150
